For those wondering how it's done, see the CSS:<p><a href="http://timeforzen.com/images/sharecounts.png" rel="nofollow">http://timeforzen.com/images/sharecounts.png</a><p><pre><code>    #sharetwitter {
      width: 90px;
      background: url(images/sharecounts.png) no-repeat right -20px;
      margin-right:16px;
    }
</code></pre>
Nice hack.

Well I'm told that newer versions of perl optimise alternations internally and this is redundant now:<p><pre><code>   my $re = join "|", @list;
   my (@matches) = $txt =~ /$re/g;
</code></pre>
Quicker and faster...
